reviewText: The East side Kids volume 7 brings back great memories of a group of kids doing the right thing in society. Protecting those who needed help and helping the police to capture the criminals

Digitally Restored Double Feature, Volume 7 of 7. Critics' Choice has 14 of the 21 "East Side Kids" movies, as seen, on Turner Classic Movies Channel. THESE seven Volumes are c-l-e-a-r-l-y the most-clear releases of these films, second -- only -- to the new: 1.)===> The Bowery Boys: Volume One 2.)===> The Bowery Boys: Volume Two <==last 2, of these 12 movies, are in W=I=D=E=S=C=R=E=E=N! Don't confuse The DEAD END KIDS / EAST KIDS / THE BOWERY BOYS. They are --- mostly --- the same four or five guys who age and/or get replaced from the '30s through 1956's last film with Bernard AND Leo Gorcey; 1957's film where David changes his last name, back, to Gorcey. From 1957-1958 The "Boys" are: Huntz Hall; Stanley Clements; David Gorcey & Eddie LeRoy... to the, d-e-a-d [excuse ME!] end. SHOULDN'T be any more confusing than the SIX Three Stooges, right? Who's on First!
